HBO the cable channel still exists, and it's always been called HBO to my knowledge. They still air shows on this channel, including Euphoria and The Last of Us. The clue, which specifically uses the word "airer" to indicate broadcast television, is correct.

You're thinking of the streaming service, which is a hot mess.

@Steve L

Very admirable summary! And almost completely correct: HBO Go was an early video-on-demand streaming app, back before *subscription* video-on-demand existed. The app distinction is key, because VOD existed prior to apps – as part of a cable tv package.

After HBO rebranded Go to Max, a number of other streamers branded their offerings as "Max" as well. Because why make distinctions and make things *less* confusing for your users?!

